DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(87)90028-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X87900286
AB  - This study tests hypotheses about the valuation of leasing contracts. We examine the determinants of the yields of a relatively large, reasonably heterogeneous, and nationally representative sample of financial leases. We find lease yields to be significantly related to treasury bond yields and our proxies for the systematic risk of the leased asset's residual value and the transaction and information costs associated with the lease. There is also some evidence of a relationship between lease yields and the default-risk of the lessee.
